Nara can unfold her inner senses to discover what is often undetectable by conventional sensors. Aside from physical objects, Nara can see echoes of past events or so-called memories, and even track the life energies of other pilots. Her attuned senses allow Nara to see echoes of the Aether overlapping with our reality. So, while the Aether spirits guide her, Naras needs define what echoes she perceives. While it doesnt require an actual mental image, Nara must genuinely accept the need for what she must find.

<span size="14">Press</> <gameaction id="ActivePower0" width="54" height="54" offset="8"/> <span size="14">to uncover things around Nara that she needs and that others often cannot see. </>|<span size="14">Hold </><gameaction id="ActivePower0" width="54" height="54" offset="8"/><span size="14"> to reveal points of interest and activities within a wide area around you and mark them on the star map.</>

For a limited time, Nara and Forsaken can enter a state of perfect synchronicity to execute drift maneuvers at impossible speeds and angles. Using her gifts, Nara accumulates spirit energies that Forsa wraps around his hull. Inside this energy fold, both are protected from their maneuvers extreme g-forces, which would normally crush every human pilot and tear apart even Forsaken's frame. While other Elders and their ships have entered a drift trance on rare occasions, only Nara and Forsa can drift at will.

<span size="14">Hold</> <gameaction id="Drift" width="54" height="54" offset="8"/> <span size="14">to maintain your current movement direction and speed. While doing so, you can aim in any direction.</>

Nara and Forsa can move into the perfect position to strike and overcome all barrier fields within the blink of an eye. Faster and more agile than any known ship technology would allow for, they become the ultimate hunter. For this Rite, Nara manifests the primal fear of a predator surprising its prey. Focusing on this unconscious terror allows Nara and Forsa to dash across the Aether connections between all present and past beings. For a fraction of a second, they leave our reality and reappear where their enemy fears them the most.
<span size="14">Press</> <gameaction id="ActivePower1" width="54" height="54" offset="8"/> to instantly leap at a valuable target destination, even through barrier fields.
After leaping, temporarily overcharges Rite Energy capacity.
After leaping, all weapons and Rites deal 50% additional damage for five seconds.

Nara manifests the suppressed, emotional and instinctual impulses lingering around her, collimating them into a raging storm. These bursts disrupt her enemies energy supplies, rendering them vulnerable and incapable of fleeing or returning fire. Even the Faceless corruptive energies are no exception to this. Despite no human-made weapon being able to scratch the surface of Corruption Clusters, Nara can shatter them with ease.

<span size="14">Press</> <gameaction id="ActivePower2" width="54" height="54" offset="8"/> <span size="14">to disrupt enemy shields, thrusters, and weapon systems  and destroy massive Faceless Corruption Clusters.</>
Disrupts multiple targets in a chain reaction.
Temporarily overcharges Forsaken's shield by the amount of damage inflicted against hostile shields.

Nara and Forsaken turn into a falling star, spearing through enemies and impenetrable surface fractures with the heat of a supernova. With this Rite, Nara focuses on her enemies' anger and suppressed rage, manifesting these energies into our reality as a pure, destructive force. While they might take her for a blazing star, it is, in fact, their own hatred that burns them.

<span size="14">Press</> <gameaction id="ActivePower3" width="54" height="54" offset="8"/> <span size="14">to gain extra speed and spear through enemies and structural fractures, while is heat heavily damages even close by hostiles.</>
Increases the destructive heat area by adding four more stars.
Destroying an enemy will partially repair Forsaken's hull.

With this Rite, Nara can hold enemy ships and throw them like explosive projectiles, though she does not apply any physical force. Instead, Nara taps into the unconsciousness of humans or advanced machine AI's. There, she applies a spiritual force, transcending the distinction between mind and matter. Under her control, the pilot and ships themselves crave to be thrown at their maximum velocity. The Rite is a well-guarded secret by the Great Prophet, and Nara is the only Elder who can master it after her exaltation.

<span size="14">Press </><gameaction id="ActivePower4" width="54" height="54" offset="8"/> to hold an enemy. Press <gameaction id="ActivePower4" width="54" height="54" offset="8"/> again to thrust it into another enemy or obstacle.

<IH1>I should buy that missile launcher first.</>

Did you think I wouldn't find out?
So disappointing. And you know what I do to those who disappoint me.
<IH1>He took everything personally. For him, the Circle's goals and his own were one and the same</>
It's been a while since I've been back here.
So you were an orphanage recruit? What was that like?
When you've seen the things I've seen What they did there
I am now. The Elders they gave me a reason to go on gave me a purpose in life.
<IH1>They once gave me purpose until they didn't.</>
And you guarantee my family's safety?
Join us. We're all one family here. And we look out for our own.
They have a choice We can be very convincing.
Right No need to worry about us. We'll do it!
<IH1>I used to be VERY convincing, too.</>
Elder! What do we do when heretics talk with us?
You talk. And do your best to share the Prophet's teachings about the Chorus.
And if they don't want to listen?
<IH1>Mejem was a true believer. And I believed in her.</>
Did you hear? It was brutal! Nara took down so many--
Whoa whoa, keep it down! I don't wanna get caught talking about her, bad <I>or</> good! She scares me!
She's scary alright. And amazing! With her on our side, it's like we can do anything.
<IH1>They loved and feared me and they followed</>
Hey, don't you ever want to go somewhere new?
Do you still want to go to Amarok?
No. Ever heard of the "Blue Planet?"
It's supposed to be beautiful and has all kinds of people.
I hear it's a dead world Those people destroyed it.
Sad I guess people are the same everywhere.
That thing that creature. It appeared again!
Yeah. Very. What should we do?
I don't know report it to Arvo?
The first settlers didn't fear the Faceless.
Arvo! Those creatures we saw, they're back!
Okay. Get close, and shoot one down. We need a sample.
Stay safe. I'll catch up soon.
The settlers they shot at the Faceless first.
Reckless and sadly typical of humans.
Keep close, the creature's up ahead!
No, my shots missed like the target just disappeared.
I wonder why the Faceless didn't shoot back?
It probably did not perceive them as a threat.
Ugh It was all so fast
It's not an ordinary creature It changed itself and vanished. I'm sorry.
Like a nightmare! It looked like a dream I'm having, alright?
Irreversibly damaged. Yes. So is humankind.
It's all about war it always was. We're so good at finding new reasons to kill.
Why? So we can just send them out to murder again?
<IH1>And yet he sends them so easily now</>
Peace perfect harmony I've seen it. It's real!
Harmony, that's the key it will cleanse all our pain! We must live as one united
If we face all our demons, only harmony will remain and peace
I don't need luck! I've destiny on my side.
Are you sure you want to do this?
Why are we fighting alongside these nightmares.
They're the heretic's nightmares. Not ours.
But they're horrors. It's all so wrong!
If you want to leave, then do it now. You know what happens if they
Are you ready? Because I am!
I can feel it his ship
But I held the ship. For a second! You try it.
<IH1>Awaan strictly insisted power must be disciplined. I rebelled, but I should thank him now.</>
I'm so tired I haven't had a break in months!
But what else can we do? Join the pirates?
Why not? What we get paid over a month, they loot in a week In one week!
Maybe not I should do it.
<IH1>And what you'd have to do to get your credits faster</>
What's its name again? The Enclave?
Catchy, right? People need a safe place.
And you'd be perfect as our "Chief of Security."
Ha! Not so fast, but show me around.
<IH1>I think Sav was selling more than the Enclave.</>
Curious. It's not my firepower that makes these Regrowth Seals react.
No, machine. It's my gift empowering you.
<IH1>I was wrong. It was us together.</>
Hey, have you heard anything from your sister? Isn't she in the Sira system?
Last I heard she was headed for Amarok.
Amarok? Oh no! I heard the Circle is cleansing that whole system.
What Really? I've gotta warn her!
Hey, I saw something very strange.
Ships that looked like nothing I've ever seen. They're definitely not ours.
I've seen them, too! Were they kind of round, with giant lights? And moved strangely?
What? No! What I saw was angular, like it was made of red crystals
<IH1>But that other sighting I wonder whose ships they were?</>
I trust you know what refusal means.
Please, Gyan, you know us. You've lived here for ten years. I promise we won't be any trouble.
It's Acolyte Gyan to you. And after I'm done, you won't be a problem for anyone.
I I can't believe it Everyone Najara it's gone.
Snap out of it, Kashee! Get us out of here, right now!
It's okay, Tonrac. She's right. I need to focus and find a way out.
There's someone! They're not with the Cult!
This is Asyx! Please help, our life-support systems--
Kashee, don't take them in! It's too risky--
We can't leave them! Asyx, we're on our way!
No! We have to save ourselves, or no one survives.
Kashee is right. We have to stand together!
Cult ships! How did they find us!
Oh, Kashee, always so naive. Thanks for saving our new followers.
It's "Prophet's Ear" to you. Now, lower your gun.
They won't. They can't break our encryption codes.
It's the Circle! You know them If they even suspect--
Asyx, listen to me. I've got your back. I always have.
Just transmit the Najara plans, and then come straight here!
Log 014 We recently discovered an anomaly, which we call a "Corruption Cluster."
I ran every test. But nothing changes it!
Its structure is unaffected by any physical force, not even the strongest gun blasts.
We need to find a way to <I>manipulate</> this anomaly. It would be perfect shielding against anything.
<IH1>If it were that simple, we'd have done it.</>
Oh, you're from the Stega Rim, right? Seems like a rough place.
Yeah, the choices are engineering or sniffing fumes in the mines.
Your new filters they're really saving us down here.
Thanks I just wish my brother Kaz was here.
We must leave immediately. Set course.
Every victory over the Cult saves more.
How did you discover the Cult's plan?
Remember our deal? You get your victory--
And I don't ask questions. Fine. But one day, you'll have to answer.
We're tasked with converting Emeq Haven. Let's move.
Oh? I used to be stationed at Emeq. I know people there.
No. It actually makes it much easier.
We must evacuate Amarok before tomorrow. Let's gather as many as we can.
There are too many Cult fighters, and we have little time.
We will not run from the battle!
<IH1>I wonder if Kardoh pulled the trigger</>

The AR-1 was once a respectable single-seat fighter. Now it is a technical throw-back that has seen more battles than most of its former pilots. Over the last seven years, Nara has taken a liking to it. Her natural skills and persistence have breathed new life into this old ship.

Forsaken is the perfect starfighter; with cutting-edge technology, advanced weaponry, and a unique, sentient AI. He is one of twelve ships, each designated to bond with a Circle Elder. But none could match Nara and Forsa's tight connection that allows only them to enter a Drift Trance at will. Together, they become unstoppable.

You can <BH1>level up</> the masteries by completing their respective goals. Each level will <BH1>increase their specific bonus</> making you even stronger in combat.

A cry for help: Distress Call
Awaan, why has Nimika always been so powerful?
First, it became a thriving trade center.
With immense prosperity came great power.
Yes. He worked to perfect and mass-produce his Tukuruq Scourge vaccine.
Rumors are that he was promised the Council's financial backing, but they betrayed him. His vaccine never left Nimika.
Allowing the Tukuruq Scourge to ravage the galaxy gave Nimika a stranglehold on trade and power.
Nimika escaped its reach by closing its borders.
They wanted him to fail and guaranteed that he did.
Awaan, why do <I>you</> think the Prophet didn't destroy Nimika back then?
After his rise to power, he decided to embrace Nimika
A public example of how his teaching could "cleanse" a people from within.
And between the Prophet's Ears and Syrys Legion, our proud heritage of fierce free will was silenced at first.
Syrys became greedy. He stole and plundered, increasing rebellion.
Many believed he had outlived his usefulness to the Prophet and would be replaced.
I was meant to replace him. But, I disappeared and Syrys stayed.
Nara, come in It's surprising what the Prophet never <I>truly</> understood about Nimika.
That your people were formidable warriors?
Quite the contrary. All cultures have their devoted warriors
We always valued artisans, writers, and philosophers far more than our fighters.
And traders don't leave out the profiteers.
Ahh yes the credit minders. That's what enabled us to pursue the arts.
And develop deep pride. Nimika people are free thinkers and bow to no one.
That's a problem there's no place for independence in the Prophet's idea of Chorus.
And that arrogance will end him.
Nara we know only Marked Ones show gifts they can channel as Rites.
But the temples are essential to enable them.
The Aether does break through in other places. The powers could also be accessed there.
But no one has ever survived the powers outside of a temple.
Unlikely. Even within Spirit Passages, Marked Ones have failed, gone mad and attacked all.
These Rites of yours are extremely dangerous to acquire.
<IH1> and they'll always remain very dangerous to everyone.</>
Nara, about the Rift at Nimika Prime what exactly do you remember?
That my Rites were critical to opening the Rift.
I felt his presence, but there was something else
Forsa, you were with me. Didn't you detect or feel anything?
Just our bond and our power. What did you sense the Faceless?
They were there, urging me on driving my emotions, my Rites.
So you could have been just an element of the opening rather than the direct cause.
Then perhaps without your involvement, another Rift can't happen.
Or my presence is no longer needed.
Nara I know the Nimika Prime Rift stopped growing, but it did not close.
Yet the Faceless are not using it.
We don't know how the remnants of the Rift function within their realm. It may only still appear on our side.
Perhaps it exists to serve as a dark warning.
We must be ready to greet them with full force
Nara we have seen the Faceless manifest in many places where there is no Rift.
They do, but they need some element of Void energy.
A focal point that allows transition between our reality and theirs.
Of course. Like the totems, ruptures, and tablet sites.
Yes, but those conduits require more energy for the Faceless to manifest in large strength.
So only smaller numbers can make it through, and they must stay near their access point.
For a large-scale entry into our Waking World, they would need another Rift.
One that dwarfs the Rift at Nimika Prime.
Why would the Faceless risk destroying our reality?
If we're gone, they go as well.
Unless they've been feeding on many life forms, moving from one reality to the next.
would be a repeating pattern throughout time.
It may simply be their purpose to manifest and feed on what sentient beings suppress.
Not all beings are inner-directed. Some act according to their true essence without judgment.
If true the Faceless could be considered to be in pure Chorus.
I'm sure the Prophet sees it that way
Ree, come in wherever you are.
When will you take over at the Enclave?
I think they should choose their leader.
I have something else I need to do first.
I must destroy the bases of the Prophet's Ears and all their spies.
And if they want out like others.
If they're still active, it's just to use the information they have against people for power, vengeance, or profit.
You can help the Enclave, and I will help you clear out the traitors.
That might work. But they must be terminated.
Awaan, what do you think of the Resistance?
They are skilled and fearless fighters.
They have their own plans and a deep hatred of the Circle.
We still believe in the hope of Chorus, its ideals, and what they can mean for humanity if pursued honestly.
And how do you ensure that happens?
The Sacred Guardians embrace a Chorus achieved through free will and dialogue. It can not be forced by tyranny
Wise plan. I hope it works.
Awaan, I hear you've been chosen as the new leader of the Sacred Guardians.
I hope I can rise to the challenges ahead. We have battles outside and inside Nimika.
There are still internal groups that secretly support the Prophet.
I can think of no one better to command. You were always the finest warrior to fight at my side.
You were my best student, and then you surpassed me. Since then, you've been my teacher.
I would not be here now without your calm wisdom.
Whatever I have to give, I will use to build our future at Nimika and beyond.
Nara do you ever reflect on your training days?
You were so quick to learn. But I recognized something unusual.
Your fighting reflexes were unmatched, but
Your true focus was on what combat could achieve rather than a thirst for battle.
I always sensed something larger waiting for me
I led many to their death
We chose you. You gave nothing but your best and treated everyone with total respect.
They died giving all they had, willingly. As would I.
For Chorus. Its ideals are real and worthy.
The Prophet started a movement, but the struggle for Chorus will outlive him.
And what happens when he's gone?
The vision expands from the one who embodies the heart of Chorus.
Right here. You are the one.
Like it or not, everything you do and say inspires humanity to strive for Chorus.
I don't know. It isn't an easy thing to accept.
Acceptance is rarely easy. And it shouldn't be.
We grew up together and were very close. Then I joined the Circle, and she didn't
One day, I went to cleanse some renegades. But I saw her there and hesitated. When I looked back, she was gone.
Yes. Later at a ceremony for the Prophet, I saw her in the crowd. And I knew
That she was special to me.
She's never mentioned you. But knowing Ree, she would protect what she holds dear.
Awaan why are there so many pilgrims gathering here lately?
Actually, this place has always attracted people.
They were drawn to its power and mystery, even before the sacred tablet was discovered.
I never really thought about pilgrims or Seekers until now.
Only Marked Ones can become Seekers, but few try. It is a personal journey, neither easy nor guaranteed.
Yes. But it is a path to power. Seekers are on a path to wisdom through virtue.
However, one path does not exclude the other, as you may learn.
When a Seeker completes their path, they become Guardians?
No. Only those who are invited take their place within the circle of Sacred Guardians.
Your numbers seem small. Do so few succeed?
Finding one's personal wisdom is difficult and often takes years to complete.
Even being a Circle Elder does not confer success.
Understood. But I don't have years.
With all your skills and inner truth, I believe you will complete your path in time
Yes. To hear the "Voice" of their spiritual companion and attune. But they don't need Rites
If the path is unique to each Seeker, how does their "spiritual companion" affect their challenge?
Their Voice must not affect the Path or instruct the Seeker.
The Seeker alone must determine how to achieve wisdom
When we face failure, our path to wisdom truly begins.
Despite my past life in the Circle, people openly trust and praise me.
Your Circle forces also looked up to you.
I manipulated my forces, just like all the Elders who served at the Prophet's side.
No you inspired true loyalty with your purity of purpose.
I think the Prophet chose you because of this.
Perhaps. But now, I don't trust people's decisions unless they're made without influence.
There is always influence of some kind.
Free will is all that matters to me now.
Forsa, I noticed something during my last Rite recovery
The Aether it's changing. Each time I visit, it has shifted or evolved.
Perhaps you are noticing more details now.
No. I sense it has adapted to me or because of me I'm not sure which.
I can't say right now. But it feels more personal to my identity, my past.
Perhaps like the Rites, each encounter with the Aether is also unique to the individual.
Perhaps But I'm wondering what these changes mean for our fight and myself.
Forsa, certain aspects within myself have been transformed and continue to evolve.
I'm more aware of many things, including you.
You once said a part of you felt missing. Perhaps it happened when you were forced inside this ship.
Or you were fragmented before they seized your essence for their process.
Such details could help us better understand the Void and bring down the Prophet.
It would be wiser to enhance my fighting power.
I was remembering the Prophet how he used to be.
You know, he inspired me at first. His teachings about a better path for humanity drew me to his side.
He became my mentor. We had many intimate talks about the future. But
as he grew in power, I caught glimpses of increasing ego, intolerance, and brutality.
It can be a heavy burden to lead. It creates internal conflicts.
What I mean is will such power change me?
It will but how you change is your choice.
You seemed very close to the Prophet.
I was Then a distance grew between us. Eventually, I became a mere spectator.
As our control over the galaxy grew, he spoke less about Chorus and more about achieving power.
And I wasn't sure if he even noticed I was there.
He did even a prophet needs someone to trust.
He was the only family I had
After Nimika, I left everything and everyone I believed in. It brought me such deep pain.
<IH1>I was broken and fled without thinking That came much later.</>
I don't believe the Faceless are living beings, like humans.
Natural forces. And they've existed only as long as humans.
Yes. And as our reality evolved, the Faceless realm did too.
Then if the human reality ends
I've been thinking about the meaning of the Faceless.
There <i>are</> strong ties between the Faceless Void and our Waking World.
Yes Since they must feed on what humanity suppresses.
The Faceless may also be a reflection of our collective existence.
Then the Faceless would reflect that change.
And being so bound with the Faceless Void, the Prophet's corruption would affect them greatly.
Perhaps their mutual corruption becomes an endless cycle, each feeding on the other.
Yes our battle must begin and end with the Prophet, not the Faceless.
Nara What was your training like?
As an acolyte, my trials were challenging, but I was never alone.
All acolytes were grouped into units of four. My unit did well.
Our final test was to journey far and recover an item that we could only retrieve if we worked as one in Chorus.
Two of them, Kisha and Urum, were my chosen wingmen at Nimika Prime.
To the very end when they died at my side.
She and Kirrim had their baby. What a great day!
Maybe but with all the threats, it just seems like one more thing to worry about.
Ahh, Nara. Look around you, at people like Ree and myself. A nice partner and even kids it's good.
I had a partner, I guess. It ended badly. Now I'm used to being on my own. It's better for me.
I hope someone breaks through that tough shell one day.
If they tried, I'd shoot them down.
Alright, I get it. Not my business.
The veteran fighter pilot? Is he around? I like his stories.
Fraid not. He died last night.
I'm sure gonna miss him. What about you?
What good would that do? But it's incredible he died an old man.
I can't imagine surviving that long.
<Sigh> I wanna leave this place lying in Ree's loving arms.
How is that a meaningful death?
Sometimes you talk in riddles, Sav.
Hmm let's check the Enclave comm-channel
Sav, we're doing our best, but it's not looking good.
Turin, people will have to do what they always do.
We can't just give up, dammit!
Nara here. Hang in there. I got your backs.
Thanks, Nara. Sorry, Turin. I know you're all working hard.
Maybe we should contact the Resistance?
Now you sound like my wife
But if we wanted to reach out, Ree has friends in a lot of places.
Yeah, good thing she's on our side.
<IH1>So, the Resistance is still out there. Opens some possibilities.</>
In the old days, Sav was something.
Strong, fearless, with such high ideals. And yet gentle.
He was still that man today.
I had done things, bad things and he welcomed me here without questions. He gave me a home.
You pick up the pieces and focus on the work.
Too many pieces so much destruction.
Honor Sav. Do what he would do. The Enclave needs you.
Yes Sav cared about the Enclave more than life.
And it's here for you, too.
I will gather everyone and start rebuilding.
There was a guy in charge called Admiral Kardoh, though I don't know if he's still around.
No Ree knows a lot more than I do. She has a history with them.
Sav said you might know something about the Resistance. Anything you can tell me?
They're still alive but retreated to a hidden base after suffering heavy losses against the Cult.
Haven't spoken to the Admiral in years. But I'll reach out and try to find out how they're doing.
Thanks. Things seem to be heating up and you never know
Yeah. Sav is always so optimistic, but I feel trouble coming, and sooner than I'd like.
Our continued isolation is not the answer.
Yes, sometimes trouble demands new alliances.
Sav and Ree are on an open channel. I'll just lay low.
Sav, I know you like to think we're somehow protected from the Cult, but
I know You're worried they're coming for us next.
And if our best fighters join them, then what?
If we have an alliance, we'll be a stronger force.
Sav, we're a target already. They just haven't aimed yet.
<Sigh> It won't hurt to secretly make contact with the Resistance I suppose.
I'm just worried we're gonna lose it all
We're a tough crowd. I believe in us.
What is the Circle doing now?
What they do best, taking over one sector at a time cleansing them. No word of the Prophet, though.
Not yet. We're too remote for them to notice.
But they are coming that's why you awakened me.
What about the opposition forces? They were always so relentless.
Elements of the Resistance have a secret base somewhere. And the threatened colonies are forming militias.
We may not survive, old friend.
Better than dying a scavenger, piloting rusted scrap.
I thought when I left you that you were powered off.
You think I am just a machine. I am aware I dream.

Why hide this away? Admiral Kardoh ordered everyone to turn over <I>all</> their equipment.
And what about after the war? We'll need this to re-build.
Not everybody here gave freely to the Resistance.
We should bring it with us.
Honey, the Resistance has enough. We'll need it later.
C'mon. We can't be late reporting for duty on our first day.
They were willing to risk their lives for the Resistance.
They were worried about their life after the war.
Then they should ensure the war is won by contributing everything to this goal.
Just thinking a life without fighting?
Whoever hears this, take what you want. I don't need it right now.
Just don't leave a mess, alright?
This generator activated the elevator's safety locks.
The elevator is stuck down there
There's probably a backup generator nearby.
Hi, Sim. I'm leaving after that fight between you and Dad I knew you'd never and now he's gone too.
Anyway, they need me at Rinak Haven.
And hey, I'm still using your old Boson Compensator. It's the best.
The mechanic didn't flee when the Cult came.
No, Dad. I am NOT joining you in Stega.
And it's chief engineer, okay? A real job!
I must get their life-support system running!
<IH1>Rinak Haven's chief engineer In her way, she's a fighter.</>
That did it, the elevator moved up again.
Okay, I get why you took it. I would've done the same.
But after the Rift is gone, could you please return it?
Press {ActionInput} to gain on the traitor
To all Cult forces, our defense grid is down. We won't resist just let us live!
Their pleas wouldn't have stopped us.
Haven Commander, why did you shut your defenses down?
Every time I reboot, someone keeps turning them off!
Our only working weapons are on this old Spirit-class ship. But our pilots aren't trained for it.
I can help with that. Heading there now.
To show their pilots its basic maneuvers.
Hang in there. I'll be back.
Commander, stream this to your pilots.
Yes-- Damn, the Cult is here!
The Circle attack will commence any minute now.
Another lesson. Let your pilots take a good look.
Tranuuk, stop your ship! Stop now!
My chief engineer he's the traitor!
He locked us out. We need his access codes.
Intercept course set. I won't kill him.
Captain of the Circle, I've locked the station systems. As you commanded
Very good. Now embrace your cleansing, heretic.
Haven Commander, you still want this traitor alive?
Then watch what happens closely This is Cult "justice."
Captain, come in! Please! My wife and kids are on board!
To the Cult, you're all heretics who must be cleansed.
I did as you asked, Captain. Stop!
Once a Resistance fighter, you're branded a heretic. And heretics must be purged.
Chief Engineer, stand down and return to the Haven.
Look at your family and think hard. Do you want them to live?
Our defenses are up again. Stronger now, with that Spirit ship. Thank you! This is for you.
Appreciated. But he won't be your last defector.
Yes but-- the Cult promises so much.
You saw the recording how they were set to purge. And not just him, but his family. Everyone needs to see this.
You failed to protect the civilian ship.
Pilot, we just received a priority one distress signal.
A weapon research facility started evacuation procedures. We must guarantee their survival.
Research facility, come in. You requested backup?
Kardoh kept his word! We're boarding now.
The Cult has already overrun our other labs!
But we need time to extract our equipment. Our research is crucial!
Alright, we'll keep the Cult at bay. But hurry.
Keep your eyes open. I'll be back soon.
More Cult forces incoming. Hurry up!
We're working as fast as possible!
Some more to go. It's highly volatile material.
We're nearly done. Only a few more containers!
I got your back. Just go and don't stop!
Nara, I only detected organic materials aboard the ship.
I don't think they were weapon engineers. They lied.
And it worked. Admiral Kardoh sent them help.
So, his reputation encouraged them to lie?
We left a reward for you at the station.
You saved years of hard work invaluable research.
All humankind is indebted to you!
This destruction Maybe the wormhole tore everything apart.
Whatever it is, let's move on.
Help-- oxygen levels-- down--- must get--
It is coming from the outpost.
Their life-support system is down, and all oxygen reserves will be depleted soon.
I cannot locate the power source while it's inactive.
This pain-- I can't focus my-- senses.
They'll have to hold on-- must get out of here!
Just an empty echo-- move on.
That corruption-- it's crushing-- my senses!
To stop the cluster's regrowth. Understood.
Something is luring them I can feel it.
Outpost command, are you still there?
Yes I'm breathing but my work
By the Blessed Stars! It's growing!!!
More corruption. I located its center.
destroy all the Corruption Hearts before they regrow.
I'll use the lightning clouds to strengthen your Rite.
Excellent. But all life signals on the Outpost are gone, too.
And now I sense something familiar. At the outpost's center.
Yes and now, no reason to stay.
They studied the Rite Aspect? And corruption?
They had no idea what they were getting into. My pain was no coincidence.
No wonder they got themselves killed.
Typical arrogance. Careless experiments have consequences.
That lightning will fry us if we enter the clouds!
Nara, we lost another base to one of those lightning storms.
But a crew member escaped. Please check on them. Ree, out.
That voice Cult Slayer? Apologies, the storm blinded our sensors.
Outpost, hold your fighters. We'll handle this.
I-- was out on patrol. But then the lightning
I don't know-- I must go back!
I'll go and check the base. You report to Admiral Kardoh. Now.
You did well, pilot. Now follow your orders.
Pilot, hold your position until I return. Nara, out.
Those are Circle ships. But, they aren't using Circle encryption.
Damn, how can that ship be here?
Their Circle ships did protect them from the lightning
Clear the area! Go, go, go!
No survivors! Take this outpost, now!
What NO! Terror incoming! Open fire!
I know. But let's report back.
Thank you. Take this for your efforts.
how long do we need to stay inside?
Until the Rift is closed. I'm working on that now.
We cannot enter this lightning field. It will fry us.
I detect something, but the clouds block specific identification. All I can verify is its designation "Soraya I."
Admiral Kardoh's ship is the "Soraya II."
This is your captain speaking. Maintain formation and stay alert--
"Captain" Kardoh this wreck must date back to when Elder Mejem cleansed this system.
The "Soraya I" could still be in here.
I sense a faint echo Could be Kardoh's ship. Let's see.
Interesting. My sensors don't detect anything.
We may abandon this ship, but not our pledge to fight
They also abandoned their cargo some containers feel oddly familiar.
Strange, these containers resonate with what feels like hunting
So they were exposed to something?
Got one. There definitely is something.
Captain. Why did we leave the payload?
There's still more I need to know.
The heretics couldn't know what a wonderful thing this is.
Ancient and new untouched by time.
But I already know this aspect of the hunt.
And I will practice it now.
<IH1>Elder Mejem left a Rite Aspect behind out here</>
I feel something, too. You're deadlier. Good
Find energy source for Rinak Haven
Anyway, we need to locate that energy signature.
Rinak Haven's survival depends on it.
I detect energy signatures. But they are too weak to pinpoint.
I sense them, too. And more
Why are they still chasing us? You dropped the singularity core in there, right?
Yes, yes, and they're swarming the place too!
<IH1>Strange, their energies show me a new memory. It's not far.</>
A dark fusion singularity like my ship core.
Then let's hope Rinak Haven can use it.
What? Get this off the station!!!
Could the singularity still lure the Faceless?
I have it contained. It creates an entanglement with the Void only when exposed.
An old civilian ship. No life signs but a signal showing Psychic Totem distortions.
I sense it too it's strange, somehow fragmented.
Negative. Despite the signal I detected, it is offline. My scans suggest the ship has been here for 125 years.
That's before Psychic Totems or even the Prophet existed.
How about rebooting its core AI?
Negative. Maybe you can sense something?
It reminds me of a totem.
Visuals, corruption-- red, red, red, bright!
We need your Rites to get closer.
Get close again. I'll try something else.
It worked! Stay near so I can reinitiate the download.
Almost. One more time, Nara. I must compensate for its fragmentation.
We need it in one piece!
I found something else in the data that might be of interest.
The ship logs indicate it encountered a Void Crystal.
Which bind our minds to the urges of the Faceless
spent a very long time out here.
We failed. But I still need to learn what it saw.
There is a chance the drone might return.
Receiving an encrypted signal. Strange it is Neju Coalition code.
Or do you prefer "Cult Slayer" now?
As long as our <I>wise</> leaders crave weapons of mass destruction, my mission continues.
You can help end this madness and avoid another Nimika Prime.
You expect me to believe you?
Believe? I thought you abandoned religious nonsense. If you want to <I>know</>, find me. Cass, out.
We received his coordinates. A trap?
This Neju Outpost? I remember cleansing it.
Yes, I sense a memory. And it's <I>recent.</>
Of course, this weapon slaughtered civilians. Intentional or not, every hit's deadly.
We-- designed it to kill-- so perfectly.
It must never be used again by anyone!
It's the colonel. I can sense his life force
I'm not sure how it's possible, but I think he created this memory just for me.
Cass is Neju, their greatest knowledge vanished in the purges.
There. That interface still has power.
Done. I unlocked a hatch, and now I detect a life-sign.
So good to see you Nara.
Do you know what I'm aiming at you?
One blast will shred your ship's hull.
No I intend to prevent another Nimika Prime. I have something to show you. Come!
Under my watch, we created a "special" weapon.
This wreck was hit with Amarit infused ammunition.
One round equals one dead ship.
Project "Werewolf." A weapon that turns any ammunition into Wolf Rounds.
And then we amplified its explosive force significantly.
They won't tear a <I>planet</> apart. But a single volley can destroy an entire convoy.
I will stop what I started. And you must help me.
Of all people, you know <I>exactly</> what will happen when this weapon falls to the Cult.
And you know it wouldn't be any different with Admiral Kardoh.
No matter what "justification" they proclaim in the end, people die.
You want me to destroy all Werewolf weapon stocks?
I did that already aside from one. When the war escalated days ago, someone stole it.
No. This weapon is far too valuable to destroy.
Then you'll own the resulting bloodbath.
If you decide to end this insanity, you know where I am. Cass, out.
At Maka Haven, a former Neju outpost. You should still find storage records there.
I'll stay low. Destroying weapons didn't make me many friends. Cass, out.
The Neju Coalition always valued science over human life.
The Prophet hated them for it He called them the "atheist scourge."
Considering the weapons they created, I understand his rage.
And yet I am a weapon, too.
Welcome back, Nara. I'm still waiting as are my weapons of mass destruction.
So, you finally realized we must destroy the Werewolf weapon stocks?
Let's hope they still have records of Colonel Cass's stolen weapon.
We could sweep their database. I found a terminal.
Nothing useful in this database, but an older Neju data storage unit is inside the cargo area.
There! A Circle ship, using a Resistance designation.
No, their surveillance is very inefficient.
<IH1>Allowing people inside, that they don't really know like us.</>
Let's see what they were after.
Get me outside, and I will pinpoint their position.
Did the Cult ship access this data?
Colonel Cass. We found three weapon stocks.
Good. That is what there should be.
Proceed as planned and eliminate them. Cass, out.
Nara, I found references to one more Werewolf container. I could try restoring the data.
<IH1>Hidden inside a graveyard of its creators</>
The "Werewolf" rounds are behind that hatch.
Negative. We need an access code.
Wait I sense a life force. Someone was here recently.
It's secure in there for now. Let's come back later.
There is a data storage module inside. It could contain access codes.
Then let's find the barrier's energy supply.
There must be another energy source.
Forsa have you ever encountered "Wolf rounds?"
Yes, pre-heated projectiles infused with Amarit minerals.
They carry intense heat, comparable to the ionized plasma of a star.
Finally time to destroy the weapons.
Any theories about what makes the "Werewolf" weapon rounds so lethal?
They are not just infused but <I>entirely</> made of an Amarit superstructure.
The Neju had unmatched scientific knowledge and resources.
Then, let's return to the Neju ship.
I'm picking up another signal. More Neju technology.
You never considered that I could have used Colonel Cass's weapon?
alone bear responsibility for their use.
You let the Circle forces escape.
A Werewolf weapon container is nearby.
One of the ships carries the payload. I cannot identify which one.
Then we'll take them all down.
No, the signal is still there.
I detect something in the wreck we passed. It's Neju tech.
Could be part of a weapon system let's see.
Good, it's not a weapon of mass destruction. We'll keep it.
I agree on keeping Cass's weapons away from the Circle.
Now they cannot use them to purge more innocent civilians.
No. But when Kardoh led attacks, he readily accepted collateral damage.
Not everyone in the Circle was a warrior.
And not every warrior was always a fanatic.
Can't shake them off! Abort and retreat!
Are you sure the Werewolf weapons are here?
Within this area. I cannot pinpoint their precise location.
Please state the purpose of your visit.
I am looking for your ordnance officer.
She's conducting an inspection over there. Should I signal her?
Yes, thank you. But I'll go to her.
No need. I'll come back later.
Moving closer, so you can access her storage records covertly.
You must be Nara. I wasn't informed about an inspection.
At ease. I'm not part of your forces.
You know, you inspire everyone by how you fight the Cult. It's impressive!
The admiral is just careful. He always says
"Traitors are the greatest threat to our unity."
Nara, I've detected the weapons. And the access codes.
No offense, but I still don't get why you won't join us--
What did he say about me?
Only to never let our guard down.
Would you mind if I take a look around?
<IH1>Admiral Kardoh didn't inform his troops about me and Nimika Prime interesting.</>
I triggered its self-destruction. Firing a weapon would have alerted the guards.
Wait, more Neju tech. But not a complete weapon.
Alright, this is safe to use. We better leave before somebody notices it's missing.
Even these Werewolf weapons would not make up for the Resistance's technological inferiority--
Right, the fight would only become bloodier.
You misunderstand. I meant that someone outside the Resistance could wield such weapons more efficiently.
Approaching the last known coordinates of the Werewolf container. But I cannot detect anything.
Feels like an echo of Colonel Cass.
Wait, I detect Amarit residues. The weapons were stored here.
So, Cass kept them. He didn't trust me.
And I certainly don't trust him with such a weapon. We must find him.
Too late we could have ended the war with it.
I told them we needed more test subjects!
They died for nothing and the killing goes on.
<IH1>The colonel paid a high price for this weapon.</>
We cannot allow the colonel to have a Werewolf weapon.
But, if we have it, it will significantly improve our fighting chances against the Circle and the Prophet.
Still if you find this last weapon, I trust you to make the right call.
Colonel Cass's outpost. He might use the Werewolf weapon on us.
No Those weapons are a stigma for him.
But he'll try to kill us.
Yes, let's end this. We must destroy the last weapon.
We'll take care of him later.
Colonel Cass. We're here. Now, where is the weapon?
I knew you would pursue any device that enhances your powers increases your kills.
I've seen who you truly are, Nara. Right here, when <I>you</> purged my people!
You <I>are</> a living weapon of mass destruction.
As long as you live-- there can be no peace!
You-- we never escape our past! Death is our payment!
My weapon-- If you kill me Nobody must have it!
It won't fall into the wrong hands.
Interesting. Despite his lies, he honored his promise that no one must use this weapon.
What do you want to do?
When we're done, I will decide about my Rites.
And I will decide about this weapon.
I trust you'll make the right choice.
Colonel Cass, come in. We have neutralized the identified weapon stocks.
Then our mission is a success!
Now they'll have to find some other method of mutual annihilation.
Apparently, my trust in you was well placed, Nara.
Please come find me. I have something for you. Cass, out.
He never mentioned the fourth weapon container.
But, I've restored the fragmented data. I know where it is.

and some Neju power cells for the Enclave.
The crew they never had a chance.

<IH1>I can still reach out with my Rite of Senses and find them</>
You really are one of a kind, Nara. How did you find that?
<IH1>They must never know about my Rite about me.</>
The lock opened. I'm moving on to engineering.
Credits might buy me a nice upgrade at the Enclave.
Careful. Automated security could still be active.
But the section is under lockdown.
I'll find a way or make one.
<IH1>I can sense the barrier fields' energy flow.</>
Good. No power, no barrier field.
So, the ARTOK it transported jump gates?
Yes, crossed space the old way.
Engineers, pioneers their families. All looking for a new beginning.
<IH1>Yes, big and slow, the perfect Circle target.</>
Moving in. I still have space for more power cells.
It's nothing, Sav. Just remembering something.
I've retrieved almost all the cells.
I knew what had happened here, but seeing it All those people their dreams, plans all dead.
<IH1>My work Once, I perfected those very doctrines.</>
Their blood is not on your hands. It's on the Cult leaders'
Get out of there come home, Nara.
Where's Ira? Is she with you? I won't leave without my baby!
<IH1>Back then, I told myself, I gave them a choice to join before I chose for them.</>
We're not gonna make it! How how the hell did the Cult find us?
My head I can hear their voices inside my head!
<IH1>No matter where you hid, you couldn't escape our their psychics.</>
<IH1>Strong resonances, here memories from the past</>
Drop the cargo, if you must.
Okay Scavenger. Hand over your cargo and maybe we'll let you go.
<IH1>You don't know what you're in for.</>
They're dead now it was their choice.
I didn't want them to follow me to the Enclave.
Understood it was the right call.
Don't think I'll ever come back here. Maybe I can still sense something.
I need to focus inside the wreck.
There are no power cells out there.
Mhm, no. I should search inside.
The power cells are in here.
People are waiting for the power cells. I need to stay inside.
We need those power cells. I should search inside.
The Enclave is counting on me. I need to find the power cells inside.
The power cells are in here. The Enclave needs them. And soon!
Don't worry. I'll keep on looking inside.
Not yet. I still need to find more.
No, I've got more to find.
The cells are only on the inside.

Amarok was fought over during the Galactic Wars for its rich resources critical to weapon construction. It is now ravaged by the centuries of war and an ancient catastrophe. It's also the last retreat for the few surviving Resistance forces still fighting against the Circle.

Through a wormhole is an abandoned research facility, first built by the Neju Coalition. Once, highly advanced weapons technology was created here, including Forsaken and eleven other sentient Elder ships. The Faceless energy in this place may have been key to their creation.

A distant system, largely forgotten since its rich resources were depleted. Even the Circle seemed to have lost interest... until now. The Enclave is the only significant population hub. Long ago, there was a mysterious alien presence. But now only an ancient temple remains.

An untamed and lonely fringe area of Stega Central, sparsely populated by free-willed loners and scavengers. It also contains the system's only interstellar jump gate, making the Rim Stega's only link to the rest of the galaxy - and a potential target for the Circle.

The Nimika system is the largest home of humanity, with a proud, rebellious history. But that pride had a heavy cost. The dormant Rift that destroyed Nimika Prime looms overhead as a dark warning and symbol of the Circle might and cruelty. Now pilgrims frequent this place while the destroyed planet's rebels still seek refuge.

A haunted place, where the Void's long dark of night leaks into our reality. It is here where humankind first encountered the Faceless and where this mysterious power chose its Great Prophet. The place of this historic encounter is now the Circle's most sacred site: the Heart.

You have to purchase the RD-26AC FIXER repair auxiliary before continuing with the story. 
The RD-26AC FIXER is a useful addition to your arsenal, allowing you to repair your ship hull in clutch situations.

You have to purchase the JAVELIN missile launcher before continuing with the story. 
The JAVELIN missile launcher has superior firepower and is like all missile launcher specially effective armor, but also has ammo limitations.
